The paper deals with explaining anomalies in time-evolving graphs, which is a problem that falls under the scope of several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper deals with communication and IP-IP interactions. The second likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper deals with anomaly detection in graphs. The third likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper proposes an algorithm for selecting pair plots to explain anomalies. The fourth likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes an objective function for selecting pair plots. The fifth likely category is cs.DB (Databases), as the paper deals with extracting key features from graphs.
